de.uni_potsdam.hpi.bpt.bp2014.database

Class DbControlNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uni_potsdam.hpi.bpt.bp2014.database.DbObject
      • de.uni_potsdam.hpi.bpt.bp2014.database.DbControlNode

  • public class DbControlNode
extends DbObject
    This class is the representation of a controlNode in the database. It provides the functionality to get the startEvent of a fragment as well as the type and label of a controlNode. Moreover it is possible to check if two controlNodes have the same output.

      • controlNodesHaveSameOutputs

        public java.lang.Boolean controlNodesHaveSameOutputs(int controlNode_id1,
                                            int controlNode_id2)
        This method checks if 2 controlNodes have the same output (mostly used for shared activities).
        Parameters:
        controlNode_id1 - This is the database ID of the first controlNode.
        controlNode_id2 - This is the database ID of the second controlNode.
